TYPE: Test,
TARGET: control module potentiometer wiring (wiper terminals),
DESCRIPTION: Test for continuity and proper connection between the wiper terminals of both potentiometers and the rest of the control circuit to verify if the wipers are effectively connected. Floating/disconnected wiper terminals can cause unstable control signals and erratic relay behavior.,
RESULT: Both the sensitivity and timing potentiometers show low-resistance connectivity ("short" or low-ohm resistive) between their wiper terminals and the (+) control input and output cables, as well as the control relay and sensor bias resistor. Both potentiometers' wipers also show normal resistive paths to the (−) control input and output cables and to the ambient light sensor. No polarity inversion is detected in these connections.
